As agreed during our conversation, I am reporting below the list of fields in the report for which a restriction has been applied due to the maximum limit of a Microsoft Excel cell (32,767 characters).

In practice, this limitation is automatically applied by Excel, which does not allow storing more than 32,767 characters in a single cell. As a result, the current algorithm used to load and transform the content of these specific fields will only process the first 32,767 characters. Any additional content beyond this limit will be truncated.

Therefore, it should not be expected that a Summary Analysis containing very large amounts of text (for example, hundreds of thousands or millions of characters) can be fully stored within a single Excel cell.

From a business perspective, if for a specific field (for example *Summary Analysis*) it is important to highlight a short summary or key information that better describes or ranks the analysis, I would recommend placing this note at the beginning of the text.
This ensures that the most relevant information will always be included and will not be truncated by the Excel limitation.

The affected fields are:

* SUMMARY_TRIGGER
* SUMMARY_ANALYSIS
* SUMMARY_CONCLUSION
* CASE_DESCRIPTION

